# Cursor Rules

# Language rules

- All code and comments must be written in English
- Variable names, function names, and class names must be in English
- Documentation must be in English

# Code style rules

- Use camelCase for variable and function names
- Use PascalCase for class and component names
- Use descriptive names for variables, functions, and classes
- Avoid abbreviations unless they are widely understood
- Add appropriate comments to explain complex logic

# TypeScript rules

- Use TypeScript types for all variables, function parameters, and return values
- Avoid using 'any' type unless absolutely necessary
- Use interfaces for object types
- Use enums for fixed sets of values

# React rules

- Use functional components with hooks instead of class components
- Use React.FC for component types
- Use proper prop types for components
- Use destructuring for props
- Use useState and useEffect hooks appropriately
- Use custom hooks for reusable logic
- Use return early pattern for functions
